        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:21PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Legend Rock State Petroglyph Site, which is 22 miles southeast of
Meeteetse, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Hot
Springs County, including the following locations... Grass Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
